Magnificent journey, we are still spitting it out. Thank you Julie!  In English, "on en salive encore" is translated as "we are still spitting it out". "En" is a preposition in French that means "in" or "of", but in this context, it is used to mean "from" or "out of". "On" is a reflexive pronoun that can mean "one" or "we" in informal contexts. "Salive" is the past participle of the verb "s'évider" which means "to spit out". So, "on en salive encore" means "we are still spitting it out". The rest of the sentence is straightforward. "Magnifique voyage" means "magnificent journey", and "Merci Julie" means "thank you Julie".
