I believe that, if it hasn't been done already, it's important that you know that you will always encounter people who may not necessarily agree with your choices, who won't like your style, your facial expressions or something else... but, never stop believing in yourself, remain as you are, with your personality and sensitivity that won over the jury; Another thing, it's not given to everyone, to dare! It will allow you to advance and we can only observe that you fit with any repertoire, I even find your versions sometimes better than the original! You seem humble and deeply kind, you have talent and generosity, you were not part of those on whom I would have bet at the beginning and sincerely, I don't remember not appreciating one of your performances, I find you surprising... in conclusion, I have loved your interpretation of Gainsbourg, I also liked the original but for once I heard the words clearly, perhaps you paid attention not to make any facial expressions, you transmitted emotion to me through my television so I don't understand how 3 members of the jury didn't feel it! Here I wish you many beautiful things, keep your feet on the ground, don't change anything about who you are, remain humble, remain you, make good use of constructive criticism and don't pay attention to those who are not.
